The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Ronaldinho for City
                                                                                                                                                                                           Ronaldinho for City
                      
	Barcelona have confirmed that Manchester City have put in an offer of 22m for Ronaldinho. There have been reports that theyve actually won the race to sign him, but those reports are being touted as bogus. According to a website, AC Milan vice-president Adriano Galliani is in Barcelona to discuss a possible deal to bring Manchester Citys target Ronaldinho to the San Siro.         
	Berbatov bid         
	 Reports said that Tottenham Hotspur have agreed a 24m deal for Dimitar Berbatov with Manchester United, but theyre waiting to find a replacement before the deal is finalised. On the other hand, contradicting reports say that Spurs are holding out for 25m. If United do go ahead and sign Berbatov, who will Tottenham replace him with? Another guy whos been linked with United, Blackburn s Roque Santa Cruz .         
	Granero joins Getafe         
	 Getafe have signed Real Madrid midfielder Esteban Granero on a five-year deal. Granero was on loan at the club last season, and he was a big part of their European success last season.         
	Ronaldo move         
	lAccording to Brazilian club Flamengo, former AC Milan striker Ronaldo is going to join the club once he fully recovers from the knee injury he suffered in February.         
	Arshavin for Arsenal?         
	lAndrei Arshavins agent has revealed that Arsenal would be an ideal destination for the Russian playmaker due to the influence of Gunners boss Arsene Wenger.         
